au Mau insurrection in Kenya. A woman displaced from Silesia recalls fleeing with children across war-torn Germany, and women caught up in conflicts in Burma and in Rwanda share their tales. War's aftermath can be traumatic, as shown by journalists in Libya and by a midwife on the Cambodian border who helps refugees to give birth and regain hope. Finally, British women on active service in Afghanistan and at NATO headquarters also speak.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aWomen and war. 0aWomenxBiography. 0aWomen. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Women.2bisacsh  aGender Studies and Sexuality, History (General).1 aArdener, Shirley, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aArdener, Shirley, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aArmitage-Woodward, Fiona, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aClarke, Marieke Faber, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCooper, Glenda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavies, Janette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrimes, Rachel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHurley, Matthew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJaschok, Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKanogo, Tabitha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSadan, Mandy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSciama, Lidia D., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSciama, Lidia Dina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSpens-Black, Hannah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:d